\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 93.} In the premises, I would have compensated Mr Raj with an award of $117,390 including the employer's 5% MPF contribution (i.e. $8,600 per month x 1.05 x 13 months) for his loss of earnings up to and including 30 September 2009.\par}

